Laura Adele Joseph, a writer and public-relations executive in New York, and Robert Andrew Mogil, an insurance account executive in New York, were married last night at the Oakwood Club in Cleveland Heights, Ohio. Rabbi Daniel Jeremy Silver and Cantor Sarah Sager officiated. The bride, a magna cum laude graduate of Duke University, where she was elected to Phi Beta Kappa, is the daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Frank E. Joseph Jr. of Shaker Heights, Ohio. Mr. Mogil, a cum laude graduate of Duke, is a son of Mr. and Mrs. Alvin Mogil of Hewlett Neck, L.I.